      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software QA documentation must meet ASME V&V 40 Gradation 4 requirements including version control, regression testing, and audit trail for Class III device at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Version control and regression testing are in place, but formal audit trail documentation is incomplete. Achieved Gradation 3 against required Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Numerical code verification must demonstrate order-of-accuracy testing and benchmark solutions at Gradation 4 for the hemolysis-coupled CFD solver.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy testing was completed for the flow solver but not for the hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) or Richardson extrapolation must be reported for hemolysis QoI at all 5 operating points, meeting Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "GCI was computed for velocity fields; hemolysis index discretization error was estimated only at 3 of 5 operating points. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating conditions within specified tolerances for all 5 flow-speed combinations at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Bench tests were conducted at room temperature rather than physiological temperature (37°C), introducing a systematic deviation in blood viscosity and hemolysis susceptibility. Only 2 of 5 operating points were tested at matched conditions. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (e.g., E%, GCI-adjusted) must be reported for hemolysis index at all operating points, meeting Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics reported for hemolysis index at 4 of 5 operating points; one high-shear operating condition lacked sufficient experimental replicates for valid comparison. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly relevant to the clinical endpoint and traceable to the absolute threshold criterion.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the accepted clinical surrogate for hemolysis and is directly traceable to the absolute threshold. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same pump geometry, blood analogue, and operating envelope as the COU at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry and a glycerol-water blood analogue. The analogue has lower hemolytic sensitivity than whole blood, reducing relevance to COU. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence and round-off error must be quantified and reported for the hemolysis-coupled solver at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error for the hemolysis sub-model was not assessed during the current credibility evaluation cycle. This factor was deferred pending access to solver internals from the commercial CFD vendor. At Model Risk Level 5, this unassessed factor represents a material epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Evidence that analysts followed documented simulation protocols and that results were independently reviewed, meeting Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Simulation protocols were documented but independent review was limited to one of three analysts. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis power-law model form must be justified against available literature and sensitivity to model-form assumptions must be quantified at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model was used without sensitivity analysis to alternative hemolysis model forms. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources with uncertainty bounds; Monte Carlo UQ must propagate input uncertainty to hemolysis QoI at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed for 8 of 11 uncertain input parameters. Three parameters (red blood cell fragility index, inlet turbulence intensity, and surface roughness) lacked quantified uncertainty bounds. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The number and statistical representativeness of experimental samples used for validation must be documented and assessed against Gradation requirements for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Sample size justification and statistical representativeness of the experimental hemolysis measurements were not formally assessed. The assessment team noted this as a gap but did not complete the evaluation within the project timeline. At MRL 5, absence of this assessment materially weakens credibility."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in the CFD model must be demonstrated equivalent to those in the physical validation experiments at Gradation 4 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the computational model and the bench experiments was not formally evaluated. Differences in hematocrit level and blood analogue rheology between simulation inputs and experimental conditions were noted but not quantified. This factor remains unassessed, constituting an epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    }
  ],
